description:
drh added on 2019-04-19 16:26:26:
The following sequence of SQL statements results in an sqlite_master table that
has one name for the table in the "name" column but a different name in the
"sql" column:
CREATE TABLE "sqlite1234" ("id" integer);
ALTER TABLE "sqlite1234" RENAME TO "User";
SELECT name, sql FROM sqlite_master WHERE sql IS NOT NULL;
This issue was reported on the mailing list by Semih Hazar.  The problem
appears to have originated in SQLite version 3.25.0.
